File: Some festive cheer for motorists, but not all will be smiling at the pumps. (eNCA) JOHANNESBURG - Motorists can expect an increase in the fuel price next month, the Automobile Association warned on Wednesday. READ: Government must invest more in public transport: AA The AA made this prediction based on unaudited month-end fuel price data released by the Central Energy Fund. The petrol price is expected to rise by 43 cents a litre, while diesel and paraffin are expected to rise by 55 cents. 